experiences.


42
00:01:58,018 --> 00:01:59,720 line:0
This could be where
we grew up in the world


43
00:01:59,753 --> 00:02:01,955 line:0
and where we live now,


44
00:02:01.989 --> 00:02:05.125 line:-2 align:center
the cultures
we're familiar with,


45
00:02:05.158 --> 00:02:08.228 line:-2 align:center
and the languages we speak
or hear around us.


46
00:02:08.262 --> 00:02:11.265 line:-2 align:center
They're also shaped
by our human characteristics,


47
00:02:11.298 --> 00:02:15.702 line:-2 align:center
like our gender, our age,
and the physical and mental


48
00:02:15,736 --> 00:02:19,106 line:-2
abilities and disabilities
we might have.


49
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:21,141 line:-2
You can think of each
of these factors


50
00:02:21,175 --> 00:02:24,745 line:-2
as its own diversity axis,
and the intersection of where


51
00:02:24,778 --> 00:02:29,850 line:-2
someone lands on all these axes
makes up their unique identity.


52
00:02:29,883 --> 00:02:32,352 line:-2
It's a good reminder
to think critically about


53
00:02:32,386 --> 00:02:35,088 line:-2
how people with completely
different identities


54
00:02:35,122 --> 00:02:39,259 line:-2
and perspectives will all be
able to enjoy what you've built.


55
00:02:39.293 --> 00:02:41.562 line:-2 align:center
When someone approaches
your app or game,


56
00:02:41.595 --> 00:02:44.464 line:-2 align:center
they should feel like
you designed with them in mind.


57
00:02:44.498 --> 00:02:47.768 line:-2 align:center
Not only will people feel taken
care of, you'll build trust


58
00:02:47,801 --> 00:02:52,039 line:-2
that extends to other areas
of your app, game, and brand.


59
00:02:52.072 --> 00:02:53.540 line:-2 align:center
One of the great things
about being


60
00:02:53.574 --> 00:02:55.943 line:-2 align:center
in your position is
that you're in charge


61
00:02:55,976 --> 00:02:59,379 line:-2
of how accommodating
your designs will be for people.


62
00:02:59,413 --> 00:03:02,382 line:-2
It does take
work and consideration,


63
00:03:02,416 --> 00:03:04,618 line:-2
and you're not always
gonna get it right,


64
00:03:04,651 --> 00:03:06,687 line:-2
but any intentional steps
you take


65
00:03:06.720 --> 00:03:08.989 line:-2 align:center
will be appreciated
by so many people.


66
00:03:10,390 --> 00:03:13,627 line:-2
To help, we're gonna talk about
how to approach designing


67
00:03:13.660 --> 00:03:18.031 line:-2 align:center
inclusively, especially
in the area of content.


68
00:03:18,065 --> 00:03:21,368 line:-2
At Apple, we define
"content" as the words,


69
00:03:21,401 --> 00:03:25,105 line:-2
images, audio,
and video that live


70
00:03:25,138 --> 00:03:28,242 line:-2
inside your designs,
as well as your marketing.


71
00:03:28.275 --> 00:03:31.945 line:-2 align:center
Content is the language you use
to speak to your audience.


72
00:03:31,979 --> 00:03:35,215 line:-2
And it's also how you let
folks identify themselves.


73
00:03:35,249 --> 00:03:38,252 line:-2
This can be through the names,
profile details,


74
00:03:38,285 --> 00:03:40,988 line:-2
avatars, or characters
that people can customize


75
00:03:41.021 --> 00:03:42.789 line:-1 align:center
within your app or game.


76
00:03:42.823 --> 00:03:45.492 line:-2 align:center
The way you address people
through your content


77
00:03:45.526 --> 00:03:47.961 line:-2 align:center
and how you let folks
represent themselves


78
00:03:47,995 --> 00:03:51,598 line:-2
are great moments where you can
make more people feel welcome.


79
00:03:51.632 --> 00:03:53.567 line:-2 align:center
So with that,
